snippet: Alphabet replaced Google as the publicly traded company that will house Google’s search and web advertising businesses, maps, YouTube and its “moonshot” ventures like driverless cars.
abstract: Alphabet replaces Google as publicly traded firm that will house Google's search and web ad businesses and other ventures.
lead_paragraph: Alphabet replaced Google as the publicly traded company that will house Google’s search and web advertising businesses, maps, YouTube and its “moonshot” ventures like driverless cars.
